Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You share what you've learned and try to bring it to the words of people.\NAnyway, I don't know whether he did or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.60,0:01:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I suspected that, you see, I knew Helen.\NShe got it from interdictation, and I thought there was a translator.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.49,0:01:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought from Christ to Helen, there was a translator that translated\Ninto a level that comes out at 600, which is at least reachable by human authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.54,0:01:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There go the invisible helicopters.\NWait a second, because this doesn't bring up a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.70,0:01:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, spiritual truth stands on its own.\NIt does not stand on the reputation of the speaker of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.10,0:01:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is the truth, whether Jesus spoke it, Buddha, or Nero.\NTruth is truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.42,0:01:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if Adolf Hitler said, loving your mother is good, it's either true or it isn't true.\NIt depends on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.36,0:01:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't depend on who says it.\NSo the truth that's caused miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.22,0:02:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It does not depend on whether Jesus Christ is its source or not.\NI always felt that there's a tone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.80,0:02:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a shift of tone in the textbook as compared to the workbook.\NThat shift in tone is what I was objecting to before.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.64,0:02:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What it seems to be a pitfall of setting up a duality, a positionality, and a polarity\Nand viewing the ego as an enemy to be vanquished or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.10,0:02:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that came somewhat from a different consciousness on the other side.\NIt's a little different view than the workbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.71,0:02:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The workbook seems more pure to me.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.25,0:02:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I never calibrated the two compared to each other.\NMy guess would be the workbook would calibrate higher than the textbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.86,0:02:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The textbook is great in explaining many things that you couldn't get out of the workbook.\NThe workbook gives no explanations at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.16,0:02:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just something that sounds mystically ridiculous.\NYou get what you get out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.70,0:02:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless you.\NThe textbook at least gives explanations.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.46,0:03:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So that you can grasp it perhaps better.\NThe only defect, as I say, I don't think you want to set up a polarity with the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.29,0:03:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the whole problem with spiritual development then is one of polarization based on positionality.\NThe whole ego is based on positionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.70,0:03:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It cannot exist without positionality.\NThe minute you have an opinion about something, you're screwed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.58,0:03:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I think.\NJust add it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.54,0:03:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the 12-step groups say we have no opinion on outside matters.\NAnd the power versus force, I use the 12-step groups because they are to me really the paradigm of the purely spiritual,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.22,0:03:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the pure spirituality as different from religion.\NReligion becomes dogmatic and secular interests.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.59,0:03:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,12-step groups have no secular interests.\NThey don't own anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.99,0:03:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't own any buildings.\NThey have no pomp or circumstance, no money.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.93,0:04:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all poverty-stricken, all the groups.\NAnd they have no position on outside matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.80,0:04:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That was extreme wisdom.\NSo the source of the 12-step groups is real spiritual genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.50,0:04:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no positions on outside matters.\NAnd those spiritual traditions throughout history that have taken no secular positions have survived the purists.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.74,0:04:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddhist teachings of the Buddha are the teachings of the Buddha.\NAnd.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.54,0:04:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And they still remain in 900.\NBut so the purity of the teaching then is partly based on having no position on outside matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.54,0:04:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So I myself don't have any position on outdoor matters, outside matters from a spiritual understanding.\NI can take it apart and see how it's put together.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.15,0:04:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not a criticism.\NI'm just saying that's how it's put together.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.07,0:04:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how it's put together.\NIt's neither right nor wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.49,0:05:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, China is where it is because that's the evolution of that culture.\NI mean, the leader, don't forget, the leader of China is as much a prisoner of his culture as everybody else.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.25,0:05:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He can't just say anything willy nilly that he wants to right off the bat.\NHe's held on by a whole tradition of culture that goes back thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.41,0:05:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He can't just say, blah, blah, blah, you know, no way any more than the leader of our country could get up and just say anything comes off the top of his head.\NSo he can't just willy nilly go out there and violate all kinds of premises that have been, you know, enculturated for many generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.55,0:05:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So he's not.\NSo you can't blame one leader for, you know, he's a product of his own culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.39,0:05:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's part of our compassion is understanding that part of our compassion is understanding that consciousness is innocent.\NIt's like the hardware, the computer, and everybody is the prisoner of his own software.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.31,0:05:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody is the prisoner of his own software.\NEveryone is the victim of his own software.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.13,0:06:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of condemning people, we feel compassion for them because we can see they're run by their software.\NAnd they don't know any differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.47,0:06:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you about 700 on the planet?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.24,0:06:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know who they might be or where they're living?\NThere was a guy named Dick Brody there at Clarkdale that was running the cement business there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.78,0:06:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And he moved.\NNo, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.94,0:06:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But what we do is we get, we're trying to get the overall balance of spiritual energy on the planet.\NSo let's just ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.28,0:06:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,There are beings on the planet who calibrate over 1,000 right now.\NThat's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.29,0:07:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God, there is.\NI think the last thing we found was over 900 is four people, something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.60,0:07:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,At one time, there was 12 that calibrated over 700.\NTwelve at 700 totally balanced the total negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.80,0:07:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time.\NI wrote the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.00,0:07:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Totally balanced the counterbalance of the negativity of all mankind.\NOne in 1,000 counterbalances the entire negativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.74,0:07:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Four at 700, yes.\NThere are a couple of people right now that calibrate high 900s, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.72,0:07:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you calibrate Sai Baba?\NNo, I want you folks to do that kind of thing, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.81,0:07:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the legendary Indian figures that everybody goes oohs and ahhs over, when you calibrate them,\Nyou'd be surprised what you discover.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.86,0:07:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all hearsay.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.05,0:08:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But people go by as sort of a myth, spiritual myths.\NMyths.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.39,0:08:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's repeated from one person to another, especially in new age groups.\NCertain names bring all kinds of ahhs and oohs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.65,0:08:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You calibrate them, there's nothing that are ooh.\NThe reason I want to teach people the technique is so that they use it because you'll be driven
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.72,0:08:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to use it if you have your own curiosity.\NIf I answer it, I'm extinguished.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.72,0:08:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Your curiosity and now your motivation to learn how to use it for yourself is gone, see?\NBut really, if you really want to put what we said today into practice, other than saying
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.94,0:08:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to China, I do would like you to take all the books in your library and see which ones\Nmake you go strong and which ones make you go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.00,0:08:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And those that make you go weak on this side, it'll answer your own, see?\NAnd you don't have to look at the name on the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.92,0:09:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This book here, this book is over 500 resist, over 600 resist.\N610 resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.84,0:09:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This book is at 600.\NI don't know, you know what it is, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.84,0:09:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to read the name because I don't want to suggest any thoughts to myself or\Nanybody else.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.84,0:09:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I can turn it upside down and just calibrate everything.\NThen you turn over the cards and see what you've got.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.84,0:09:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\NAnd a really amazing awareness dawns on you, how you've been.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.73,0:09:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how does that happen?\NIt has to do, the White Brotherhood was transmitted by, what's her name?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.85,0:09:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Alice Bailey.\NAlice Bailey.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.85,0:09:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, okay.\NThere's one there called Glamour.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.01,0:09:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Excellent book, excellent book.\NIt's the glamour of a lot of these supposed gurus that you're sucked in by, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.97,0:10:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Glamour is a negative energy, is an energy.\NGlamour is what gives certain media figures great power over large populations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.97,0:10:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because they're glamour, not because of who they are.\NWho they are is nothing really.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.97,0:10:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But they have learned how to present a certain glamour.\NIt's the glamour of certain spiritual figures that appeals to people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.61,0:10:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Glamour.\NAlice Bailey.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.05,0:10:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Alice Bailey.\NYeah, it's a series of books.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.24,0:10:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all gone in blue.\NSupposedly channeled from the White Brotherhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.30,0:10:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one of those I wouldn't go for just because it's channeled by the White Brotherhood.\NI mean, I don't care who it came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.68,0:10:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm still going to calibrate it.\NSo, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.64,0:10:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Glamour is an interesting spiritual awareness that people are...\NYou see, because if your hardware has no built-in safety mechanism,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.77,0:10:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,your hardware has no built-in safety mechanism,\Nhuman consciousness cannot tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.84,0:11:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,To this day, the population anywhere in this world cannot tell truth from falsehood.\NI can persuade, because I know the tricks of all the trades,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.99,0:11:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,how to imitate that which I know will attract them,\Nbecause I know what they're attracted to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.12,0:11:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I will become that which I know is influential to them.\NIt's like I could sense with you, let's say I could sense with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.12,0:11:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that only a big fat person with a beard would have any influence on you.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.60,0:11:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can come on like that big fat person with a beard that you would then respect.\NAnd you would give me...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.72,0:11:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I don't have that power.\NYou give it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.72,0:11:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You give it to me.\NBecause you fell for glamour.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.72,0:11:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the glamourization of all these spiritual figures,\Nyou say, what the fuck does this guy know?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.72,0:11:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't even have a turban on or a white shirt.\NHe doesn't even have a hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.72,0:11:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't even have a turban on or white clothes or sandals or nothing.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.97,0:11:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I spoke at a group one time, and they had several speakers,\Nand they were all dressed up like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.13,0:12:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought, God, Jesus.\NWhoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.55,0:12:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NI mean, how did Jesus dress?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.55,0:12:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NIf Jesus were alive today, what would he appear on television?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.55,0:12:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a question I always play with.\NWhat are you going to achieve with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.55,0:12:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a lot of hair?\NYes or no?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.84,0:12:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NHow are you going to achieve that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.84,0:12:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, we take out light fixtures.\NI mean, would he drive a car?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.84,0:12:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, how did he get to the blazer and all that?\NYou see our images?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.84,0:12:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How they are, what I'm saying is the image.\NSo, how would you recognize that which is Christlike?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.84,0:12:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that which is Christlike is probably walking down the street looking like nobody.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.84,0:12:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Another thing I think I said in the book and I'll have to explain, is,\Nyou can't trust the man in the suit if you don't have a tie.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.24,0:12:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I modified that a little bit in the book.\NI did modify it a little bit in the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.24,0:12:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was very interesting.\NI think I modified that a little bit in the book, but the way it came out originally in my awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.22,0:13:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is you can't really trust a man in a suit and a tie. Let's see.\NGenerally speaking, that is a fact. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.84,0:13:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Generally speaking, that is a fact. Now why is that?\NWell, because the minute you put on a suit and a tie,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.18,0:13:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you have just bought into a whole different ballgame of what goes in society.\NSee, the minute I become part of the establishment, the business establishment, the governmental establishment,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.05,0:13:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,a whole new set of rules applies now.\NSpinning the truth a little bit is part of the whole game. It's accepted.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.45,0:13:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody knows that politicians spin the truth a little bit.\NEverybody knows you have to cut a few corners to make a few bucks for the stockholders
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.76,0:13:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,or else you're going to be president of this corporation.\NAm I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.94,0:14:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You automatically have to be part of a whole different culture with a different truth than spiritual truth.\NThey're not committed to spiritual truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.51,0:14:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They're committed to pragmatism, showing a profit, expediency.\NExpediency is the law there. Not God, but expediency.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.93,0:14:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just greed, it's expediency. Expediency.\NThere's a magazine sitting in our hotel room that says,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.08,0:14:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,How I Saved a Billion Dollars.\NSweetheart, we should read this before we leave the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.03,0:14:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We've saved a billion dollars.\NGod, geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.59,0:14:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's mind-boggling, isn't it?\NWhat would you do with a billion dollars?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.67,0:14:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, God, your life would be a nightmare unless that happened, isn't it?\NWhat do you really need or want?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.30,0:14:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if I inherited a million dollars, if I suddenly came into a million dollars,\NI'd have a couple of dents on my car I'd take out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.22,0:15:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the kind of life I'd like, and it has a few dents I'd like taken out.\NAnd then I'd rebuild a chicken coop.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.78,0:15:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, in reality, that's really how your life is really run, isn't it?\NI mean, there's a couple of dents that probably got in the car you'd like taken out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.98,0:15:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't know what we'd do with a billion, sweetheart.\NI don't know what we'd do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.23,0:15:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, I wouldn't give it to anybody because it corrupts them.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.23,0:15:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you give it to?\NWhat would you give the billion to?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.23,0:15:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Your own children?\NYou'd be condemning them to hell, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.52,0:15:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The worst thing that can happen to anybody is to win the lottery.\NYou read those statistical analysis on what happens to the people who live in the lottery.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.52,0:15:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's horrendous, you know?\NDivorce rate is 60%.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.78,0:15:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Suicide rate is 35%.\NBankruptcy is like 42%.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.87,0:15:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's incredible.\NThe worst thing that can happen to you on this planet is to win the lottery.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.87,0:15:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just horrible.\NIt crushes people.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.87,0:15:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It demolishes them.\NIt's horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.48,0:16:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's God telling me how to save a billion.\NCalibrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.98,0:16:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Would that affect the...\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.98,0:16:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll speak to the objectivity of the kinesiologic test, which I first wrote of in a fascinating\Nvolume you'd love to read called,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.98,0:16:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Quantitative and Qualitative Analysis and Calibration of Levels of Human Consciousness.\NI'll keep you up late at night working.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.98,0:16:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,With a very impressive statistical analysis in which P was less than 0001.\NVery impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.33,0:16:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If P is less than 001, that's very impressive.\NP less than .01 is very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.33,0:17:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If P was less than .0001, staggering, correct.\NAnyway, in which we scientifically validated the reliability of the kinesiologic method.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.89,0:17:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty in understanding kinesiology is because we tend to think of ourselves as\Na body, and we tend to think locally, and we think of causality as what causes things
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.89,0:17:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to happen is local causality.\NSo when we look at kinesiology, it seems to us like what the test subject is thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.98,0:17:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,or feeling must be influencing the result.\NWe personalize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.75,0:17:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So in a curious way, we anthropomorphize that which is not human, because consciousness\Nis neither human or non-human.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.75,0:17:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's neither male nor female.\NIt's the unmanifest out of which all of evolution evolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.12,0:17:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a non-local phenomenon.\NIt doesn't depend on human.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.02,0:17:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't depend on the person's personal opinion.\NNow I did a, to clarify this, I did a, I remember a videotape in which I used children.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.34,0:18:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I used a child, she was an eight-year-old or a ten-year-old, and she had no knowledge\Nof any of the things we were testing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.34,0:18:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,She never heard of Saddam Hussein or Adolf Hitler or anything like that.\NAnd we would just put a picture of somebody in an envelope and hold it over a solar plexus
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.34,0:18:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and she would go weak.\NAnd if it was like Abraham Lincoln, she would go strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.34,0:18:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So she had no knowledge of what was there.\NAnd then we did something that was in opposition to prevailing human belief systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.29,0:18:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We held organic tobacco.\NTobacco that's raised organically without any pesticides.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.29,0:18:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you tested out kinesiology, organic tobacco that's raised without any pesticides\Nmakes you go strong, much to the surprise of everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.58,0:18:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody thinks, oh, tobacco will make you go weak, huh?\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.58,0:18:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Standard manufactured cigarettes will make you go weak, yes.\NSo we did some research.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.58,0:18:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We found that up to 1957, tobacco products did not make you go weak.\NAfter 1957, they did.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.58,0:19:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was apparently due to the fact that they put some kind of a pesticide, some kind\Nof chemicals on the tobacco as it grows in the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.58,0:19:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And from 1957 on, it was injurious to most people.\NPeople in the Course in Miracles, we know better.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.25,0:19:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We know what we hold in mind is what we're subject to.\NSo if you think cigarettes will kill you, goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.25,0:19:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If they have nothing to do with you or reality, then you can smoke them.\NSo unless you've taken the Course in Miracles, I don't think a person could smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.25,0:19:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I'm sure the prevailing thought system will give them something bad.\NBut anyway, we had this little kid holding all this tobacco.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.25,0:19:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, she went strong.\NSo I mean, that was about, in other words, what they're showing is the complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.25,0:19:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, adults will do the same.\NIf we put organic tobacco in a package and they don't know what's in it, it makes them go strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.25,0:19:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And a package of Lucky Strikes will make you go weak.\NSo I would say, unless you've done the Course in Miracles, you probably should avoid smoking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.25,0:20:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I saw the paper this week, and there was a thing left.\NIt said, you know, statistics from California showed that the incidence of cancer of the lung has gone down 14% in the last decade.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.25,0:20:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Due to its fierce anti-smoking campaign, etc.\NOf course, if the death rate from that has gone down 14%, I've got news for you folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.44,0:20:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The death rate from other things went up 14%.\NYou've still got to get off this planet one way or another.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.60,0:20:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So 14% of people listen and take this exit out.\N14% more are going to be taking that exit out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.60,0:20:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,See what I'm saying?\NSo it's just an interesting way of looking at things.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.82,0:20:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You said before about conscience.\NWhen a person leaves this, they're at a certain calibration.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.98,0:20:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's not going to change.\NSo if you believe that the soul, the individual conscience,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.02,0:21:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is part of the whole, evolves, how can it evolve,\Nif its consciousness is 200 and it dies and it stays at 200?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.49,0:21:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,An interesting thing you can discover is that every infant, the instant it's born,\Nalready has a calibratable energy level.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.44,0:21:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The instant it's born, come in at 300, come in at 200, come in at 50, come in at 400.\NWhen you look at the nature of consciousness, which is beyond time and place,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.82,0:21:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you're periodically incarnate.\NYou incarnate into physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.82,0:21:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Because only apparently within physicality, I've researched this all out,\Nonly apparently in physicality are certain things learnable, let's say.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.98,0:21:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you're committed by thinking that you're physical to the physical domain, whatever it is.\NConsciousness, then we also discover that consciousness evolves about five points per lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.61,0:22:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Every person's consciousness goes up five points in a lifetime.\NI think in the book, Omniology, this fellow brought up some interesting statistics.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.11,0:22:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd researched that he found the average number of lifetimes that it takes\Nto get to the point where you don't have to come back anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.11,0:22:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was 58 times or something.\NI didn't have a chance to check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.11,0:22:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I wrote a review of the book, I didn't check out everything I read,\Nbut he'd gone into some things I'd never had time to look at.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.14,0:22:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd said the average human being has been here 58 times before,\Nthey don't have to come here anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.14,0:22:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose there's slow learners and fast learners.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.18,0:22:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably some people get it the first time.\NI said you don't have to redo the Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.18,0:22:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What I meant is you can read it 50 times, and then once you get it.\NSo you only can read it once.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.18,0:22:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You really only get it the one time, because now you've got it, you've got it.\NPeople will read it over and over again, and then suddenly in one instant you get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.59,0:23:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in that instant that you just did the course.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.59,0:23:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You were looking at the course before, but now you really took it.\NYou see, when we're sending love to the leader of China,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.86,0:23:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't something you've got to sit down, put both feet on the floor, and fold your hands.\NYou know, like doing Est.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.86,0:23:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All of you did Est, remember that?\NOkay, both feet on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.86,0:23:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, now put yourself on space, and cross your hands.\NIt's a funny little thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.86,0:23:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to do that.\NYou can just be peeling your potatoes, and you think sort of, just send them a loving thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.86,0:23:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what the hell?\NThat guy's got a hell of a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.86,0:23:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NYou just send a little bit of loving human compassion.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.96,0:23:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, what a job.\NImagine facing the karma of this guy when he goes to bed at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.96,0:23:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A quarter of the population depends on his every judgment and thought.\NWhew, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.96,0:24:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know, all those little things are how we do our spiritual work.\NSometimes it gets defined as such a structured, heavy-duty sounding kind of deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.89,0:24:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to sit cross-legged, breathe in certain ways, you know, and not eat meat,\Nand all those kind of stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.89,0:24:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, oh, the hell with it.\NI'll do it some other lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.89,0:24:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\NIf I have to wear sandals to get to heaven, I mean, I, you know, I can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.89,0:24:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So you mean after the person dies, they have some kind of meeting, and they make some kind\Nof decision about how much they learn, and how much they do?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.88,0:24:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know that.\NI don't know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.88,0:24:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just saying, from the science of consciousness, it's obvious that you have a calibrated energy\Nfield.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.88,0:24:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd where you're going after you leave the body is going to be pretty much determined
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.98,0:24:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,by what your calibration is.\NFirst of all, anything less is going to be obnoxious, so you're not going to be attracted
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.98,0:24:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to that.\NAnd anything too high is not going to be meaningful, so you're not going to be attracted to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.98,0:24:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to be attracted pretty much to where you understand yourself to be, because\Nwhat we tend to see is our self projected out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.23,0:25:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand what I'm saying?\NIf you see yourself as loving this, then that which is loving this in the next domain is
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.47,0:25:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're going to be attracted to.\NYou see?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.47,0:25:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,If getting high and killing people is what your thing is, you're not going to be attracted\Nto heaven, because that would be looking very boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.74,0:25:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I talk to a lot of these kids at the girls' ranch, you know, about peace.\NI've learned not to use that word.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.74,0:25:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace is not what anybody on this planet really wants.\NYou know, they talk about peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.74,0:25:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy gives a lecture on peace, and goes out, and somebody drags him to the fender\Nof his car, and he's in a raging fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.74,0:25:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't really want peace.\NIf he wanted peace, he wanted peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.74,0:25:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted peace.\NHe wanted peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.74,0:25:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted peace.\NHe wanted peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.74,0:25:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted peace.\NHe wanted peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.74,0:25:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted peace.\NHe wanted peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.74,0:25:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted peace.\NHe wanted peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.74,0:25:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted peace.\NIf he wanted peace, he'd say gee, I'm sorry that happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.44,0:25:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And gosh, here's my insurance card and here is yours, and you can't drive 10,000 miles\Na year without getting a bump.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.45,0:25:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not possible.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.23,0:25:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the compassion for the other person's problem?\NYou understand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.79,0:26:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Compassion is feeling sorry for the other person that they just goofed, you know ?\NYes, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.88,0:26:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You said the average person just goes up five points in a lifetime.\NWhat about people like us who are really working hard at it?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.08,0:26:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I just did a statistical average.\NNo, people like in a group like this will probably go up hundreds even in a lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.20,0:26:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never asked, but I've experienced myself jumps that were well into the hundreds.\NSo people that are spiritually committed, I think, can precipitate.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.68,0:26:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say, you grow, you evolve slowly this way, but also you can make very sharp, sudden.\NYou know, Zen is based on sudden awakening.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.93,0:26:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Zen is based on sudden awakening.\NMy own experience was very sudden.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.93,0:26:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Each of the things that occurred to me occurred spontaneously.\NAll of a sudden with no warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.28,0:27:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,One minute you're in one domain and an instant later you're in a totally different domain\Nwith no warning at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.67,0:27:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Just bang, all of a sudden.\NAnd you're overwhelmed by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.05,0:27:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't function.\NIt's just very awesome at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.05,0:27:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what is left of the ego witnesses the opening of the light coming in and it's blinded for a short period.\NThere's a moment in which you're stunned out.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.05,0:27:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just stunning.\NAnd it's like a stunning shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.12,0:27:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you spend all your life in caves and suddenly you walk out into the brilliant sunlight.\NYou suddenly can't see.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.37,0:27:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember it was quite a stunning shock.\NAnd the nervous system had a hard time handling it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.59,0:27:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Very hard.\NIt wasn't built to handle that kind of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.25,0:28:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So spiritual evolution is probably perceived at the rate at which our karma and our capacity can handle it.\NSudden jumps could be quite incapacitating, I think, without some preparation.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.23,0:28:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And suddenly there's no mind, no thought, no thinginess.\NAll this profound silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.19,0:28:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The focus is different.\NThe focus, when you're in the ego state, you're focused on form.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.28,0:28:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're focused on sound.\NAnd you're focused on logic and significance and all those kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.99,0:28:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're not in ego, you're not focused on sound.\NYou're focused on silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.14,0:28:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And what I hear, I use the term hear all the time,\Nis a profound silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.14,0:28:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,My perfect environment is one in which is absolute silence.\NThe Hotel Romeo right now is fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.55,0:28:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely silent.\NBig carpet.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.55,0:29:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Just silent.\NAnd the sound is all wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.55,0:29:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, some people, that would drive them crazy.\NThey come and visit you in your house in the country,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.92,0:29:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and after three days they can't stand it.\NBecause of the sound of the streets and the people and the direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.92,0:29:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the mind.\NThe mind, I mean, whatever you call that, that is there now,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.09,0:29:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is into non-form.\NIt's into silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.64,0:29:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And it takes energy to focus on the world and the form that it insists you pay attention to.\NIt's exhausting to tiring.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.72,0:29:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There is an energy that translates what that means.\NSo that in the silence there is an awareness of what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.08,0:30:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But it seems to take energy.\NAnd so a lot of things don't get done.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.13,0:30:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they just, they're not, it's hard to do.\NYou can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.84,0:30:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Like balancing your checkbook.\NYou don't have to bother balancing your checkbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.99,0:30:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you realize that?\NYou don't have to bother.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.02,0:30:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You get a checking account that if you overdraw it,\Nit pulls it up here, it charges it to your charge card.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.02,0:30:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And that way if you don't get any notices, you know you're okay.\NIf you get a notice,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.18,0:30:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,they just had to transfer $100,\Nthen you put a minus 100 in your checkbook and now you know where you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.18,0:30:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So unless I get an overdraft debit notice,\NI figure the figures are probably all right so I never do more of those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.18,0:30:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But there was a time when I couldn't have slept.\NCouldn't have slept if the checkbook wasn't balanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.94,0:31:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So those are just the fun things.\NWhat do you do if you're alone in town?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.97,0:31:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to calibrate something.\NIf you're alone, the reason I recommend kinesiology with two people
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.80,0:31:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is because there's an energy between the two people\Nthat doesn't exist when you're by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.87,0:31:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, the person that you use as a test subject habitually\Neventually becomes very psychic, very adept at pulling.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.87,0:31:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're thinking about, they will pull the answer out of the universe\Nand say to you, what about so-and-so in a plant?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.87,0:31:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That was it.\NWhere did you get that?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.87,0:31:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So there is a benefit to two people in working with the same person all the time.\NThere are techniques which people use by themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.80,0:31:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the strength of the ring, pulling on the ring to see.\NBecause the energy of truth makes you strong
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.80,0:31:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and its absence makes you weak.\NSo if you say, my name is George,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.80,0:32:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess that was not the truth.\NWhat the world calls me is Dave, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.53,0:32:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The world seems to call me Dave, not George.\NThat's what it says.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.53,0:32:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So there is that technique.\NThen there's techniques where you can just resist pressing your fingers together.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.53,0:32:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So people have different techniques.\NWhen you've done kinesiology a lot, you can tell by the sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.53,0:32:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as you ask the question, you get a sense of what the answer is already.\NYou can feel it run down your arm before your arm even goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.53,0:32:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,before the muscle even reacts, you already will get an answer.\NIt's just, I feel it run down my arm for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.53,0:32:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Or it even hits.\NSo there is that technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.27,0:32:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There are other techniques.\NThe book Omniology, Dr. Lee,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.27,0:32:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Lee, not a circle,\NDr. Lee,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.27,0:32:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,recommended was, well there is also one I knew of by the Hawaiian,\NI can't think of the name now.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.45,0:33:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They had a calibrated level pretty much like my scale,\Na number of inches from the body of the person's aura.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.45,0:33:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And I guess they would douse it,\Nthe width of the person's aura.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.45,0:33:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And they would come up with similar characteristics.\NThe loving person's aura radiates out.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.41,0:33:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Lee suggested a method of where you hold a brick.\NYou hold a brick in your hand like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.41,0:33:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you hold truth in your mind,\Nit's easy to hold the brick up.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.41,0:33:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you hold something that's not truth in your mind,\Nthe brick is hard to hold up.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.41,0:33:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You get very tired holding it up.\NSo there are other techniques that people use.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.00,0:33:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You can train any part of yourself.\NYou can train any part of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.00,0:33:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a matter of training too.\NI must train my arm to be a pendulum too.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.00,0:33:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say, your name is George.\NHe says, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.65,0:33:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Your name is not George.\NIt's a fact that your name is not George.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.65,0:33:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, that's true.\NMy name is not George.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.87,0:34:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NSo there are some people that feel faint.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.87,0:34:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There are people that can tell they're in the solar plexus.\NA lot of times if you look at your solar plexus,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.16,0:34:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll get the answer right away.\NJust the feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.19,0:34:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The sensitivity in your solar plexus.\NPeople get that sixth sense, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.21,0:34:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in cosmopolitan areas.\NI can remember walking down 10th Avenue in New York City
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.72,0:34:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and I heard footsteps somewhere down the block\Nearly at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.72,0:34:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And my solar plexus instantly knew\Nthat these two guys were muggers.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.17,0:34:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I instantly knew who they were.\NMy solar plexus told me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.17,0:34:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So when they asked for a match, I laughed at them.\NI said, yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.55,0:34:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And they laughed back at me that I knew\Nwho they were.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.55,0:34:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NYeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.55,0:34:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSure.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.58,0:34:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought there was something interesting on TV\Nthe other night about the electroencephalographic study
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.41,0:35:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,they'd done on the difference of the cerebral metabolism\Nbetween men and women.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.41,0:35:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see that?\NThat was really interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.41,0:35:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In a conversation, in a man, only the left hemisphere goes on.\NIn a woman, both hemispheres go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.41,0:35:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that interesting?\NIt explains a lot of human phenomena, for one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.89,0:35:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because to be a man, you have to cut off your feeling about stuff.\NYou can't go out there and shoot people and kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.89,0:35:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't shoot and kill and be a soldier and all that kind of stuff\Nand also have feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.92,0:35:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No way.\NOh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.92,0:35:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You shut it off.\NSoldiers, stand up there straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.92,0:35:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.\NI don't give a rat if your mother just died today.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.92,0:35:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Just stand there.\NI mean, you don't say, hey, my mother died today.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.92,0:35:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,For Christ's sake, I'm telling my mother.\NAre you a soldier or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.92,0:35:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've got to learn to shut off all that emotionality.\NYou can't function in the male world if you're going to be in a feeling-ness state.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.99,0:36:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,A woman, biologically, functions best when her feeling-ness is there.\NIt's her feeling-ness for her children and her family and for her country
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.85,0:36:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and for the qualities of life.\NThe woman traditionally stands for the qualities of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.88,0:36:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,A man is supposed to bring in the capacity, but she gives it the quality.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.10,0:36:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,She gives it the meaning.\NSo she engenders meaning and significance and quality into life, whereas the man just
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.10,0:36:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,brings his practicality.\NHe brings you a dead animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.10,0:36:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,There it is.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.10,0:36:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.10,0:36:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NI'm wearing this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.10,0:36:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NCome on.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.10,0:36:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, she's supposed to make it into something attractive and nutritious that uplifts mankind\Nand doesn't give you nausea when you look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.10,0:36:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but he's supposed to not have any feelings.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.10,0:36:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He's supposed to be able to shoot the deer.\NIf you open up your right brain and look at a deer, you can't kill it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.10,0:36:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no possible way.\NYou look at a deer and you realize that it loves its life to the same degree that you
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.20,0:36:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,love yours.\NEvery animal loves, is a person, for instance.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.20,0:36:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a person.\NAnd it loves its own existence to the same degree you love yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.20,0:37:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No more, no less.\NOnce you look into the eyes of the deer and see who it really is, you can't kill it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.71,0:37:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't kill it.\NSee, you can't hunt and also have your right brain moving on.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.71,0:37:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't do it.\NThe minute your right brain opens up, you can't kill another deer, unless it's the last
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.74,0:37:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,deer you ever kill.\NYou can only kill a deer when you've got half your brain working.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.09,0:37:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got total brain working, you can't kill anymore.\NYour killing days are over when your right brain opens up.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.22,0:37:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, it's an incredible beauty.\NI remember one time I was stag stinging the pasture ground where I lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.25,0:37:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And he stood up there and said, it was so incredible.\NIt's magnificent.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.28,0:37:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the incredible beauty.\NIt's the incredible beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.28,0:37:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's standing there.\NIncredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.51,0:37:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Gorgeous.\NBeautiful thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.51,0:37:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And the thought of killing it is just like unbelievable.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.63,0:37:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what holds up the evolution of consciousness too.\NBecause your love for all that lives then would constrain you from a lot of negativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.63,0:38:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's only by cutting off that love that you could possibly kill another human being.\NSo when people are not involved in consciousness, we use right and wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.36,0:38:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Right and wrong.\NBecause they lack spiritual awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.36,0:38:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So we tell the child, you know, it's wrong to cross the street without holding mommy's hand.\NThen we give them a spank if they do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.23,0:38:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They need right and wrong because they don't have any sense of reality.\NA mature person looks down at the street and looks up and now I see there's a truck coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.23,0:38:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a truck coming.\NThey don't walk across the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.23,0:38:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Not because it's right or wrong, but because they have a sense of reality.\NSo if people are not involved, we have to tell them killing other people is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.71,0:38:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And when they're more involved, it wouldn't even come to your mind to kill somebody.\NIt would be ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.80,0:38:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you call it if you like killing somebody?\NI always say, you can tell you're making spiritual...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.90,0:38:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I always say this in every lecture.\NYou can tell you're making spiritual progress when it gives you great pleasure to let somebody in in traffic ahead of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.90,0:39:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody's trying to get in and you say, ah, come on in.\NGive them a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.90,0:39:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because your pleasure makes you feel good to do that.\NYou know you're making progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.90,0:39:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You're over 500.\NYou've got to be at 500 to really enjoy letting people get in.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.90,0:39:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, really genuine joy.\NYou can see the happiness on their face.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.90,0:39:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it just knocks people out.\NEvery time I do it, you have to think, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.90,0:39:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Wave the hand frantically.\NI mean, it's the most wonderful thing that's happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.90,0:39:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's made their whole day.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.90,0:39:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what our schedule is.\NYou'll have to keep me on score.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.38,0:39:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.01,0:39:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So we've got to what?\N15 minutes left.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.01,0:39:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we're going to do the book time.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.01,0:39:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody have any more questions?\NWe'll stay as long as people have questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.01,0:39:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I have one for my son.\NHe's seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.01,0:39:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was really sad thinking that I was going to die one day.\NAnd he said, why do we have a body and why do we have to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.01,0:40:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wondered if you had an answer for that.\NWell, those are certainly good questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.01,0:40:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we have a body and why do we have to die?\NWell, apparently the body ceases to exist as a living entity.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.01,0:40:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So we know, speaking of death then as a physical phenomenon, we know that all that arises\Non this planet from life expires from life.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.88,0:40:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So we know that the physicality, so the source of the body is the universe.\NAnd we know that the physicality is going to arise and cease.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.48,0:40:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So when he says die, you'd have to say, well, what happens when the flowers drop off and\Nthe leaves drop off the tree in the fall?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.93,0:40:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Is they go into adornment?\NIs they go into a dormant period?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.93,0:40:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And after the dormant period, they renew their energy and they burst forth again with new\Nlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.38,0:40:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what Dr. Lee said in Omniology.\NIt was rather interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.38,0:41:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, what happens is we energize, we come back into another physical body and the human\Nlife and the vicissitudes are pretty exhausting.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.08,0:41:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And we leave it, we go into a period of dormancy where we like renew our energies.\NAnd once our energies are renewed, we're ready to resume the growth pattern again and we
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.15,0:41:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,get reborn.\NSo it'd be like spring and fall, sort of like we go into a period of dormancy and then
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.34,0:41:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,reemerge in the spring with renewed energy, renewed understanding, renewed commitment.\NAnd that was his explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.44,0:41:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's probably as good as any I've heard.\NThere's another way of looking at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.40,0:41:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So long as you identify self-care.\NIdentify self as the ego, which is the physical body and mind and structure and form, then
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.40,0:41:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you would reincarnate that which you think you are, which would be another body.\NSo long as you think you're a physical body, you'll reincarnate as another physical body.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.91,0:42:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that's your identification of who you think you are.\NIt would be attractive to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.79,0:42:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Does spiritual growth take place only during physical manifestation?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.79,0:42:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Eternal spiritual growth takes place all the time.\NI haven't done much research on the so-called inner planes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.46,0:42:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, what goes on between incarnations.\NMy presumption is that consciousness being what it is, it continually seeks to evolve
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.80,0:42:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,itself with or without form.\NOne of my guess would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.22,0:42:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Those that are committed to spiritual evolution in the body would certainly be so with the\Nsame auto body, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.22,0:42:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a likelihood.\NBut that's just a guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.82,0:42:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.\NDo we go to school between physical lifetimes?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.16,0:42:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We do.\NWe do.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.77,0:42:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we do.\NIt's always been taught that we sort of go to school on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.22,0:42:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was presumed that that was the fact.\NThat you had probably spiritual duties to do, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.22,0:43:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe greeting new souls as they come across and they're coming from culture shock, you\Nknow?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.41,0:43:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking they're a physical body and they finally are not.\NAnd you've got to handle their grief and upset over that.
